# Mortar Follow-Up Plan

## Goal

Break the mortar polish/gameplay request into small, independently reviewable changes.

Requested changes:
- Mortar impacts should deal friendly fire at the normal damage rate.
- Mortars should render a visible black shell projectile fired from the mortar.
- The shell should read like an overhead arc: compressed near launch, stretched near midpoint,
  compressed again before impact.
- Autocast mortars should avoid firing at target points where friendly units or buildings would be
  damaged, assuming friendly units hold their current positions.
- Dust cloud animation should be doubled in size, thicker, and last twice as long.
- Change the mortar explosion color from orangered to orangeyellow.
- Mortar wheels should be slightly thinner, less circular, and more pill shaped.
- Mortar legs should use the owning player's team color.
- Selected Mortar Teams should display their firing range as a dotted line.
- When Mortar Teams have autocast enabled, the Fire hotkey on the command card should show a
  swirling autocast animation.
- Right-clicking the Mortar Team Fire command-card button should disable autocast.
- Attack preview red dotted lines and crosshair should use a darker hue.
- Mortar attack previews should remain visible until the mortar round hits.
- Multi-selected mortars should support holding `X` / fire hotkey and clicking repeatedly to fire
  multiple mortars without the second click deselecting the group.
- Scout cars should get the same repeated hotkey-click behavior.
- Reflect the final behavior in the relevant design docs.

## Phase 1 - Friendly Fire And Autocast Safety - Done

Server behavior:
- [x] Change mortar AOE resolution so friendly units and buildings take the same impact damage as enemy
  entities when inside the mortar impact radius.
- [x] Keep fog/event projection safe: friendly fire must not reveal hidden enemy positions to players
  who could not otherwise see them.
- [x] Update autocast target selection so a mortar rejects an attack point if any owned unit or owned
  building would be inside the damaging impact area, using current positions only.
- [x] Keep manual fire dangerous: player-commanded mortar fire should still be allowed onto friendly
  units/buildings.

Tests:
- [x] Mortar impact damages friendly units at the same rate as enemies.
- [x] Mortar impact damages friendly buildings when inside radius.
- [x] Autocast refuses or skips a shot that would hit owned units/buildings.
- [x] Autocast still fires at valid targets when no owned entity would be hit.
- [x] Manual fire can still be ordered onto a point that contains owned entities.

Patch notes:
- [x] Mortar shells now cause full friendly fire.
- [x] Autocast mortars avoid shots that would hit your own current unit/building positions.

